The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Golf camp concludes
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Golf camp concludes
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Top women golfers of the country participated in a seven-day long intensive camp conducted by the IGU ladies section, which concluded at Royal Calcutta Golf Club (RCGC) on Sunday.         
	Seventeen golfers, besides promising players like Gauri Monga, Gurbani Singh and Laverry Kumar along with four other city girls, took part in the training session which dealt with the psychological and mental toughness of the players. Siddhi Kapoor, a 10-year old from the city, was the youngest participant.         
	Supervised by former national champion Indrajit Bhalotia, the training comprised an hour long yoga session in the morning followed by the golf sessions and video analysis.                                                                                                                          
